al signs including muscle tremors, abdominal<br>pain, incoordination, respi=
ratory distress, and recumbency, then<br>death. Diagnosis can be made by an=
alysis of postmortem samples for<br>ammonia content and of suspected source=
s for non protein nitrogen<br>content; ruminal pH > 7.5 is supportive of th=
